string_value: After waiting on hold for 30 minutes I was told I needed to make arrangements to log in at a KP facility which is more than a 2 hour drive each way for me.   On Sunday I called back (just to double check) and talked with someone else who luckily was able to get the passwords to sink-up and resolved the problem within 20 minutes.

I submitted this request 7 days ago. I used the follow-up chat function with Matthew and he had me submit a new request. I asked if I can have this worked on now, but he said I would need to wait. So basically I am waiting even longer with no better timeframe of when it will be addressed and possibly resolved.
IT unable to fix the mail access right away, needs 4 hours or more to do it.

I appreciate that each person I worked with owned the problem and stuck with it until we got resolution which included asking for other resources as needed.  It took about 2-3 hours in total to solve it and they were successful.

This was a tuned query which needed to be fixed quickly so our physicians can look at data every morning. Varun Vasudev has used newer and better approach to fix the SQL code and reduced the runtime under 3 minutes.

Jun responded to me right away. The request was on behalf of a senior leader who needed her laptop fixed. We tried to fix virtually, but needed to be rebuilt. Within 2 days it was complete. I am always happy when Jun gets my tickets~!!!
Problem resolved quickly however wait time for assistance was 45 minutes.  Unacceptable when trying to run an operational department and need access to files and Teams meeting app.

The IT guy listened to my concern and was friendly. I have tried to complete this task b4 but was not successful. When I looked at my KP learn today there is no outdated classes. I appreciate the prompt service too. Thanks so much best experience so far and I’ve been here 6 yrs.

Needed help on 12/09/2021.  
Wasn't contacted until 01/20/2022.  
ServiceNow - means service in 2 months, not ok.

still waiting. It refresh is has not restored my Q drive when the changed out my computer. this is impacting patient care., scheduling reviews . this is unsatisfactory response 8 day and still no response?
8 days still waiting. IT refresh failed to install the Q drives on their refresh. this is impacting patient care, schedules, reviews, etc.  not satisfactory response at this point.
I tried setting up my voice message today and it keeps asking for my ID.  What is that?  I asked this question 6 days ago and still haven't gotten a response and still cannot set up my voicemail.

While my account has Ordway but I am an 1800 harrison employee working remote, Daniel listened to my issue prior to transferring it to 1800 and was able to help me with my issue.  This was important to me as I needed to access the network to prepare for a meeting today.  I appreciated his taking the time to listen briefly and then provide help prior to just rerouting me to 1800..  Thank you.
the service agent was no help send me to the website and not explaining nothing after a 40 minute wait

With the challenges facing the management team due to COVID, I find it out that KPIM has not allowed a longer period then 5 days for access approval.  I need to get two managers to approve the request and 5 days is not a responsible timel.

Only problem was the timing of when I heard back..  I needed to figure something out early in the day, and didnt hear back until after 10:30am. By then we had already decided to switch out the laptops. I dont know if that can be helped

The IT person on the phone was helpful and pleasant to talk to. I called at 7pm because my computer was not working and I needed it for patient care the next morning. They came at 8 am the next day to take the hard drive and returned it back around midday, so I only had to use a laptop for a little while.
inability to resolve my issue and I was told it would be resolved 2 months ago.  Also, when I call, you do not listen, you interrupt without  hearing the entire issue

I initially submitted the request in Sept and then again in October finding out that an attachment was also required (not familiar with the process).  No one would respond to multiple requests around ETA on either service request for the next few months.  Build was finalized on 2/2/22.  Would have liked a chance to review before it was put into production as there were some missing items.  Response time to those issues were quick.
Incredibly quick and personalized service--did not even need to leave my office! Got problem resolved within 24 hours. Exceeded all my expectations.

The day I called in about this issue Monday January 3, 2022. I was told that I would be contacted the next day and I was not contacted at all, just an email with the case information and no resolution three days later on Thursday January 6, 2022. The resolution was that the website was "working as designed" which I take as it is not supposed to be working at all which is odd and completely irresponsible to not inform the people that use it and need it for their personal information and use of. I am not happy with just being ignored and that is why my review is of the lowest rating of Not at all likely and Not satisfied with this service I received.

The IT person, Alex, told me that I needed to disconnect from global protect and shut down my computer and that if my password didn't work to call the service desk.  I did this but because I was working virtually which I told Alex, I was completely locked out and could not sign back in.  I had to drive 45minutes round trip to go to a Kaiser office to connect to the Kaiser wifi so I could use the temporary password.  Alex completely messed up and told me to disconnect when they should have given me a temporary password prior to disconnecting from global protect.  They cost me an hour of my time and gas money because they did not give me correct instructions or a temporary password.  Absolutely am not satisfied with my interaction with Alex.

My concerned  was  resolved  by my colleague  ,Dr Pham,Technology lead . IT  service  was fine, but I was told by IT person to go check other coworkers' computer screen and  how their tool bar was activated , take  that snap shot and email to him. I do not  think that  is  appropriate  response  and  told him that it  is his job to figure out if he does not know and  to get back to me.   He  did follow up with me  next day ( for   that  I gave  him  4/10 ),  but  problem was  solved  with help of Dr Pham.
I still can't access mainframe. I have had technicians remotely re-install it on the computer before so not sure why I need to wait 10 days before it gets fixed on this computer.
quick response and fixed the problem within 10 minutes so the provider did not have his clinic day disrupted

wasn't able to solve my problem and was not able to work 5 hours out my 8 hour VMC shift and had to stay late to try to make up the lost time. I was told a specialist was going to call me back, but never got a call. I ended up figuring out the problem myself. I needed to disable my monitor audio as an option for sound output. For some reason, the cisco phone app was outputting the sound through the monitor even though the plantronic headset was selected in all the settings.
Long wait. Spoke with an agent. I was provided with a phone number that's no longer in service to call for my issue. I had to call the helpdesk back and waited another 30 minutes.

Curious as to why the entire CO region was not made aware of why the access was taken away from up for "compliance" issues.  And that it took IT 24 hours to figure this out, What is the reasoning for this major change?

Problem outstanding for 2.5 months, has never been resolved

Regarding rating the IT person--I don't know who that person was...

I requested assistance via 'Chat with IT' which prevented me from having to wait 30 minutes on the phone. The issue that I had was detected and forwarded to another team that promptly remedied the problem.

I placed an initial call for IT services and the individual was not able to help and he was going to have a local IT call me back.  This was 0800 in the morning.  I did not get a return call and had to call IT back when I completed my shift at 1430.   The second IT support person was able to quickly resolve the issue.  This impacted how I do my job.  I am a consulting nurse and was having issues with Avaya phone.  could not take phone calls for the day.

Situation was not resolved. On Friday 1/7 Sasha IVanisevic asked me to call and they would leave the ticket open for 30 days. On Monday 1/10 Kevin M. Mack  closed the ticket before I had a chance to respond. One working day is not 30 days.

I opened this ticket 13 days before I saw any movement on it.  I noticed that the ticket was passed off to other assignees over and over again who all commented "Work in progress" but yet it still didn't get completed.  This was unacceptable.  I had to reach out to the person it was last assigned to in order to get it taken care of.  Not a good way of doing business.

the technian, Monica who worked when Health Connect team was closed, did now know how to help. She worked with me about 25 minutes and we thought it didn't work but later I called the patient and it appears it did work. I wish someone would tell Monica. I don't know how or why it worked. She did her best.

The issue in not fixed. the cables are not adhered to the wall properly and my chair and my foot still gets caught in it. 
I have asked for this to be taken care of over 9 months ago. many requests put in.  I think I may have to do it myself to prevent my own injury.
could not access mainframe . password did not work and over 60 days since I used it.
Sending me a job aid doesn't resolve the issue. I already had the job aid and the primary dx had been set and it still was not populating. 19 days later.....

There was miscommunication between the BP and the tech. I sent a step-by-step document to help the tech to get to the problematic documentation on a Saturday but was not used by the tech. Tech was in a hurry to resolve the problem by telling me that I documented it. Not thorough. The problem was stated incorrectly. First time I rated a service with 1.

It took 3 days to get the issue resolved.  I called the incident in on a Friday morning around 0445am and as of Monday morning at 0700 we still didn't have the issue resolved.  I requested my department manager to follow up with IT help desk with this ticket number to expedite the repair at that time (0700). I work night shift so I was not here when the IT representative came in to resolve this issue Monday afternoon. Thank you

The tech worked on the possible solution. It would have taken approx. 2-3 hours for the updates to happen. I had requested to keep the ticket open until it's confirmed that the issue is resolved. Unfortunately, I'm still seeing the same issue and the ticket has already been marked as resolved. I will have to submit another ticket for the same issue now.

she sent me email regarding my incident number that it is fixed and has 3 business days to reply.  I dont have access to my work email at home. When I read the email, I clicked on the ServiceNow portal to reply. I could not open it and it says error. No access. I called HR and they said, they don't handle Incident numbers.  I tried to type my ticket number and it does not show on the search button.  Maria De La Pena sent me a message on microsoft team, but I could not open it because I have no access to microsoft team.  I also received an email from her that is intended to another person named Beatriz.  She's mixed up with my incident number with another person.
it took over a month to resolve and there has been 0 communication since first submitting the ticket. This also involved errors in information in a member's chart and still took 1 month to resolve.
the issue is not resolved it has been 2 months waiting to add my secure chat to normandie instead of oc

He reached out making sure to check if the issue had been resolved and completed. The first ticket I had, I followed up 2x via email saying it's not resolved no word. This one, after verifying, I was able to connect again the next day and he referred to an expert since it didn't seem to work. He followed up and made sure it is up and running. Others don't even check on you and they close the ticket.
Although she couldn't fix the problem herself, she went and FOUND someone who could and my issue will be fixed in 24 hours.  Now that's help!

Placed urgent call to KPIT for down printer affecting large portion of lab and delaying patient care immensely. Ron Deguzman came through with a rapid response and follow-up even though he was on other jobs. We were back in operation with an hour after the hardware arrived at the lab. He booked out a day to help and when lab had to postpone install 24hrs, he still made time to follow-up and dispatch alternate IT tech to assist us and work with Damon Ho all through the process. Ron gets a cookie for the day!

My issue with not having access to Cortext on my phone has not been resolved. I was told that they will contact me but looks like the ticket has been resolved today. INC13159926. I'm confused because it's still not letting me login.
I didn't have to wait on the phone for a very long wait, instead I had the option to be called.  Once getting in touch with someone my issue was resolved within 2 minutes.

Jon Gowriluk got my blank screen fixed so I could work when the first guy (on 2/2) had no idea how to fix it. It made me able to work one whole day more when I was in a remote location and couldn't get in to get a new computer. Jon also configured my new computer so it has everything from my old one.

When I called the first time, and used the automated system,  I waited over an hour, and did not get to speak to a live person. I tried again, and bypassed the auto system and got a live person, and my issue was resolved in 5 minutes.
it appears that the request fixed the issue and I have the correct access. It took almost 5 working days. Granted it was not a major work stoppage. I feel request could be managed at a faster pace.

I received an email today saying ,my service request was completed but nothing was done. I requested Adobe Reader 8 or higher so that I may use fulfillment in Microsoft edge and that did not happen. The IT service is at an all time low. It seems no one knows what to do or who does what any more. Horrible service provided.

Because she got straight to the point sent me an email and everything was taken care of within 10 minutes completely!!!! Was awesome as it is hard to do that and work at the same time. She valued my time!! THANK YOU

I'm still having the same issue with my Windows Explorer running excruciatingly slow. I keep having to restart it and restart option did not resolve the issue.. I'm on hold with the HelpDesk again. First time I was on hold for 55 mins before someone answered and my issue still remains unresolved. Now I'm on hold again for at least another 50+ minutes.

Called to request keypad/badge entry pad on both the Franklin dock door and Franklin receiving door be looked at.  Starting today the keypad portion does not work on either.  You can still badge in - but our regular drivers do not have badge access, therefore the use the 4 digit code.  This is still not working on either door.

I had to call three times and get online and escalate it.  Our department is open 7 days a week, and I could not get anyone to assist through IT.  I ended up having to ask a physician who is savvy with IT, and he fixed the issue.

the person was most unfriendly and unhelpful . He said i would have to wait 4 hours for my password it came in the email quick but didn't work and now i have to get back on the phone for another long wait.

I could not log into my computer at all and my account was disabled. I  provided the tech with both my cell and home phone number as I work remotely. I did not get a call that they had re: connected my account until I called them back at 3:45 and they said we reconnected you at 10;45 this AM.  I was unable to work at all today because they did not call me to inform me the problem was resolved.

The technician was quickly able to resolve my issue and give advice on long term solution to battery issue. I was also able to dial the Mac service desk directly by raising the ticket, otherwise I would have been a 1 hour queue for the normal service desk and was not offered dial back.

I Called yesterday, took 30 minutes to get a live person. Live person not able to fix. (we only  have this one printer in our office) I was told that a local IT person will come to check on the HP printer. Local IT only called for the printer model AM # and to route to HP that all happened yesterday, Early yesterday no one came.  I had to call gain this morning. I was not happy  that it was not fix yesterday. The HP tech came the the printer is working now.
ease of access, usually do not have time to take care of issues but today i sat and took the time and it only took less than 15 min. to assist with what kind of ticket for me to place
I have been waiting 3 days for my phone to get fixed and I'm still waiting. I need to have my phone to do part of my job.
I still have the broken printer.  It has been almost 3 months since I requested this.

After being on hold for 90 minutes, I called on another line, while still on hold for the first line, I called to say that the issue was affecting patient care, and within three minutes, the issue was resolved.
I didn't speak with anybody but my issues were dealt with and fixed within 2 days.

printer not working.  no idea if IT support is coming to see what the issue is.  IT informed it is not printing properly has variable copying. Was informed cartridge has alot of ink.  Maybe the case but has not been in operation for ~ 2 years so perhaps ink dry.  I'm not IT so someone should come out!

I never received a resolution. The RITM states that multiple emails were sent, but I never received anything in my personal email. I am not sure where those emails were sent to, but none of them were sent to me. All I received after 6 months was an email saying that the request was closed incomplete
was on hold for over 1 hour and problem did not get resolved.

The wait time was long, the recording said 20 minutes but I ended up waiting for 45 minutes.  Finally got an IT person to discuss my issues, to determine the root cause and next step took another 50 minutes.  Once the ticket was created and routed to the Active Directory department, it was resolved very timely.

30-60 mins, wait time for rep. to answer.  When answered still unable to help with major issues, could not even access KP Support to view my issues. and now I get email on monday 1/24/22 saying issue resolved because another employee is able to use the desk? so when i rotate in on Monday 1/31/22 to office, im sure i will have the same issue because its under my log on??  someone should of came in person that same day from local I.T - nothing has been resolved.... process seems useless. Also I called twice to I.T on same day, same issue with two different computers - so yeah someone should came in person on Friday 1/21/22.

MEGAN GAINNES WAS FANTASTIC AND I RATE HER A PERFECT 10. However, I spoke with a few people before her who had no idea how to fix my problem and I spent hours on the phone dealing with it. Finally by luck i spoke with Megan has more experience with MAC and fixed my issue in 5-10mintues. She should be assigned to all the MAC issues to save us all time and headache. She gets a gold star today! Please consider this suggestion. Thanks.
Less than 24 hour turn around time and my request was complete. Fantastic service!

It took 20 days to complete a shared drive access request.  This seems excessive and it was difficult as a new employee to orientate to the new department without access to our files in a timely manner.
10 months open, no communication from Team to Team, close comments are not accurate. I agreed, I use my privs to view and recommend.  DT Team configures and makes changes.
The only problem is the long wait but 16 minutes on hold until someone came on the phone
40 minute wait time when taking care of patients as an RN it is difficult to be near a phone during your shift for that long

The main desk did not seem to know what the radiation oncology department does or where we are located. Our ticket was entered under "Urology" and even though I reported we were completely down, the ticket was not escalated until 2 hours after my initial call.
The technician was able to troubleshoot my query within 10 minutes wherein I had tried to google a solution on my own for about an hour with no luck.

Wait time to get a hold of an IT rep was less than 5 minutes. .Took care of my issue in a timely manner.
Software was uploaded within four hours.
The wait time was 45 minutes.  Once I got to Kyle - he was amazing!!!!
Took care of the issue within 24 hours. This was affecting my ability to print out information for my patients in the clinic.

It takes a long time to hear back (agreement to hear back was 2 hours, I heard back in 3). The people who answer the phone initially can rarely help. I also felt  that the person who answered the phone wasn't interested in understanding the extent of the problem.

I called last week to get a charger for laptop since i only have a docking station. I asked for an urgent turn around and said I would drive to DRV to pick up. Somebody called me 5 days later. I bought one myself on amazon in the meantime.
IT understaffed, took 24 hours for resolution because no available tech on site. knowledgeable/kind staff.
Person I spoke to was able to fix the issue quickly. Only complaint is the wait time for services was long 27 minutes
it took 2 people and several work hours, but I'm glad it got fixed.
3days later...

The IT rep that was on call the day my ticket was created did not complete my task requested for 13 days. Multiple emails were shared with management and IT staff who are aware of my concern with waiting so long. All the staff who replied were helpful, but the assigned IT staff member to my ticket took way too long.

Jimmy Mofukowent out of his time to looked at my issue and take time to resolve my issue even though it was over 2 hours way his time off. 
Then Fernando was able to assist the following day and took my laptop to my department. 
Thank you for the dedication.
only about 1 minute wait to speak with the IT person

problem fixed but had to talk to 3 IT persons before I was able to get problem solved.  They all did a good job just hard to keep explaining to each tech what is the problem.  Took 2  plus hours to solve
I had an urgent issue re: Pt care and safety and it took 4 days to fix. I was told that the reason it takes so long is because someone in India had to change the printer in EPIC - ridiculous!
although my request sat in a queue for a long while, Chris was super fast, had the install complete in 5 minutes.
my problem got fixed by getting a new computer after failing to fix on my old one for 2 days! But I got what I needed :)

She said my access could take possibly 1-10 days, but I tried again for the third time into NCal prod, I was able to to get into system. A new ticket was opened, it can be closed, due to I was able to access system.
Response time on getting access to confluence was about 1 day.
Their expedient service. They were able to fix the computer problem request in less than 24 hours.

I asked for an inbox to be created, I recieved a confirmation from IT that it was created, but they did not confirm the inbox name, neither provided help on how to get it installed in my Outlook, I asked for help and is been now 5 days and no one has responded to my questions. So I turned around and ask to create another inbox and hope for the best.
The person who responded to my request had a quick turnaround time (within 2 hours). It was very much appreciated

2.5 hrs on hold to have an IT associate submit a ticket.  I was told to change my password again (this was the 5th time I was told this). Finally, Chris Solano was able to resolve it almost immediately. Chris you saved me from a literal month of battling the IT help line via phone, email and teams chat. Chris is the true MVP. Thank you.
The turn around time for my request to be completed was less than 24 hours. I appreciate that.
pleased i was offered a call back within 30 minutes rather than waiting for a lived person to talk to for that amount of time

Took 3 days to get service and now having network connection issues
getting a pop up that says "Your Kaiser Desktop logon has failed to connect drives..." Reason \\CSLSACSDC003\NETLOGON\MWI\XDMap.cfg configuration error
The woman from IT went above and beyond.  She entered the ticket for me and it was taken care of within 24 hours.  She is amazing

Super helpful!

Little bit of a long wait tho - 25 minutes
the help was immediately available, and he fixed my problem, which was hugely impacting patient care, in about 2 minutes
the analysis did not take time to look into the cause of the problem I called about, and 1 hour after she closed the ticket, the same problem happened all over again
Response time was prompt.  Issue resolved within one week as explained by IT but it was done by 3rd business day.  Thank you so much.
35 minute hold time.
can't find anyone to assist - this problem persisted for 3 days!
I was on hold for more than 2 hours

Absolutely outstanding follow-up by Igor. He was managing 2 chat sessions to update me of the status. Although he was not the technical resource, he did the best job with respect to closing the loop with the customer, that I have seen in 22 years with KP.
resolved within a couple minutes. the HOLD time was 1&1/2 hours though. Wish they had a call back system in place

I had to deal with 4 or 5 different IT support persons and took a total of 2.5 to 3 hours to get my issue resolved.  I felt like I was just getting passed around.  This whole incidence really affected my work.
I have been trying to get someone to help me figure this problem out. It took almost 3 months to get the help I was hoping for.
Having a docking station issue and a problem with my monitors at home. Both people that help took the time to walk through steps to resolve the issue which had been ongoing for 8 months
Saddia fixed it in less than 1 hour
Long wait to talk to someone (20 minutes), but when Jarrett(?) answered, he was EXCELLENT and efficient, and handled my request quickly and kindly.
Today, for the first time in 30 years, they answered immediately and helped me..... immediately.  I actually asked if I called the wrong number.  I was confused.
HAD TO WAIT ON HOLD FOR 30+ MINUTES
My issue was logged and completed within 2 hours
Fast, efficient and effective, my problem was solved in less than 24 hours. Thank you for the speedy resolution!
Help is good, but I wasted 35 minute of company time waiting on hold for a representative.
Dina was very professional, friendly and was able to resolve my problem (request exemption from 90 day email hold) very quickly by providing the resources I needed to get that request started.
Answered the phone quickly and took care of the issue.  The issue was fixed within 1 hour.  The service associate was kind and helpful!!!!  Thank You!!!!

it took 12 minutes to get connected. The wait time to get connected to a tech can be faster because as a provider we need to see and attend to patients. David was helpful and helped resolved the problem i was having with my in basket. thanks david.

Zachary Pringle was able to explain to me exactly what the hold up was with my issue and resolve it within moments. I had placed my ticket 2 days ago which was unfortunate because it was impacting patient care.
The issue took over 24 hours to resolve.
Resolved within 5 minutes

I waited 45 minutes to talk to an IT person which is poor service ultimately for our patients because I could not log in to the computer. There's a prompt for doctors only, but not other clinicians like myself who is a nurse specialist.
I have to wait 40 minutes to be able to speak to an IT person. However, Cassandra is very professional and patient in handling the issue and getting it resolved.

Replacing a bad laptop is stressful.  I wondered if I would get a host of other problems. Alain spent time with me making sure all the little things on the laptop worked perfectly.  He even helped me open a ticket for the software that needed approval.  I've been using it for a week now and its working perfectly - a first in my 14 years at KP!
no one addressed this urgent issue for over 1 month, and then it was closed without being addressed!
VERY long wait time, over 1 hour.
wait time to receive assistance.  Over 2 hours.
My ticket was resolved in less than 24 hours.  You cant ask for better customer service!
Thank you for completing request 5 months later. I forgot why I have submitted it.
Thank you for you support and quick fix although I had to wait on hold for 30 minutes. Tech was knowledgeable
Although the wait time took >20 minutes, Kevin was quick to resolve the issue.

We rec'd a new laptop in 8 days and in plenty of time before our new ee starts and Derick Vertudez called me to let me know he had it (since I'm working virtually) and to ask where he should leave it.  Thank you Derick!
The message was marked as urgent and the IT person was here in less than 30 minutes!
significant delay in responding and 3 months delay in resolving the issue.
issue was resolved in 1 day
I requested a powercord less than 24 hours ago and have already received it!  Thank you!

This request to modify a contractor's access badge was created 19 days ago and is just now being shown as closed in the system. For me, the only way of truly knowing if the request has been granted is to contact the vendor and ask him if his badge works. System seems very inefficient.
I had to follow up on my incident 3 times over a month long period before it got resolved.

Having worked with UW Medicine/Harborview Medical Center's IT people for 16 years, let me tell you what a breath of fresh air it is to work with people who actually want to help you!  5 Stars plus!  Thanks!

Easily able to chat with IT using the chat feature as phone wait time was 60 minutes or more. Andy was able to solve my problem by opening a ticket that was quickly resolved by the IT TEAM. Thank You.
Hold time was less than 2 minutes- Technician was to the point, suffice, and quick.  Took care of my problem fast.
Friendly, fast service. The individual helping knew how to remedy my issue immediately with 0 hesitation and we got it fixed in less than 5 minutes.
Was able to fix my issues within about 10 minutes!  They are always so helpful!
Answering a simple question about the licensing has taken too long - 2 months. I needed to remind IT for a few times about my request before getting the answer.
Service came too late (more than 24 hours). We need to solve the issue asap during month end.
I was on HOLD for 20 minutes
The wait was almost 1/2 hour.   But technician was friendly and knowledgable
Quick and efficient, and now my laptop works! The entire process took less than 30 minutes from the time I called to when the tech came to help. Thank you!
I waited too long for the call back. When I called the 3rd time, the number was corrected and still it took n a week before someone called me today
very easy fix from your end and less than 10 minutes to do it!  Very grateful.
The wait time on the phone was only 15 minutes, and the tech arrived quickly to resolve out equipment issue.
no response initially received -  a comment was received by TEAMS  approx 11  hours after my end of shift.
resolved the issue if 5 minutes!

Pleasant/professional and taken care of within 3 minutes.  To get to a technician was far easier than i remember it being last time i called.  there is not a whole lot of prompts to get to a technician.
Wait time to speak with a representative was 50 minutes
Juan helped me reset my password and get back to work within 5 minutes.
We had an escalated call in since it was our main pc to send out slides to our pathologist and it took 4 days for them to come and fix the pc.
Very professional and courteous and the work was done within 24 hours :}

Cassandra was quick, effective and efficient and also warm, kind and validating. Changed a stressful morning into a friendly/hopeful start to my day. Even though we connected just 10 minutes before my first patient, she was so quick there was no delay in pt care. Very grateful.
The call took 54 minutes, 47 of them on hold.
I did not have to wait on the phone 45 minutes for service

After having the phone line assigned to my name,  I have been trying to reach the service desk to set up a password for my voice mail. I have called repeatedly and always get a message saying the wait time is 30 minutes or more.  Consequently I have been unable to set this up.
He spent 2 hours on the phone with me fixing the problem. He also was engaging throughout the process

40+ minutes is too long to wait for call to be answered.
Everything else was great.
Over 30 days to get ticket resolved.
Don was so patient, and fixed the problem, even though it took awhile and required 20-30 minutes of his time.  Very appreciative!

Service took too long to address my concern. Website said my problem would be addressed in under 8 hours. 32 hours after being submitted something that took less than a minute to accomplish was still waiting for admin to perform the task
Phone was answered promptly and my issue was fixed immediately, whole phone call was less than 5 minutes. Thank you
I really liked the call-back function. It was very convenient. My issue was completely resolved within minutes and the whole process (from scheduling the callback to completion) took <24 hours.
Ernesto was fast to diagnosis the problem and had it finished and the patient routed to PCP within 1 hour of phone call.
Request completed within 24 hours.
Was told service would be completed within 4 hours it did not.  I had to send a note to the person 4 days later and it was completed.  Not sure if they forgot or didn't follow up.

The reason why I am failing the survey on the IT personnel (intermediate) is because I did not get anything done for one whole day when I got the Bit Locker prompt right after powering on in my computer at 8:00am. the 1st tech tried several things to resolve but it did not work. She expedited me to another desk and within an hour i received a msg to call them to resolve. That tech was able to resolve the issue.

also loaner never worked. It was password protected. Chad tried to help by wiping memory clean, but still never able to log on.

was over a 50 minute wait on hold; day prior was > 60 minutes. onsite service to repair/reboot laptop was great - but getting an incident ticket was way too slow. the last question is not relevant - as we can only call IT in these situations

We moved into our new building with this new printer in late April 2021, and every time the toner is low we have to call to have a new one shipped. What is the point of having this automatic service if we have to call every time the toner is low, opposed to what is promised of a new cartridge delivered when the printer begins to indicate low toner.
